ghc-mod: ghc-mod (Happy Haskell programming on Emacs/Vim)
ghc-mod:
ghc-mod: This packages includes Elisp files and a Haskell command, "ghc-mod".
ghc-mod: "ghc*.el" enable completion of Haskell symbols on Emacs. Flymake is
ghc-mod: also integrated. "ghc-mod" is a backend of "ghc*.el". It lists up all
ghc-mod: installed modules or extracts names of functions, classes, and data
ghc-mod: declarations. To use "ghc-mod" on Vim, see
ghc-mod: <https://github.com/eagletmt/ghcmod-vim> or
ghc-mod: <https://github.com/scrooloose/syntastic>
ghc-mod:
